{# ============================================================================
   HobeRadius unified CHR provisioning script -- Jinja2 source.
   Renders RouterOS v7.x configuration that is IDENTICAL across the fleet
   except for the documented per-CHR bindings. See:

     * docs/chr_fleet/06_ONBOARDING_WIZARD.md sec 6.5  -- the canonical script
     * docs/chr_fleet/06_ONBOARDING_WIZARD.md sec 6.5.1 -- which vars are per-CHR
     * docs/CUSTOMER_RADIUS_TUNNEL_DESIGN.md sec 10    -- node-role gating

   Per-CHR (renders differ between two CHRs):
     - WG_MGMT_PRIVKEY, WG_MGMT_ADDR          (control tunnel)
     - WG_DATA_PRIVKEY, WG_DATA_ADDR          (data tunnel)
     - WG_DATA_ADDR_IP                        (data tunnel IP w/o /mask)
     - ROUTER_IDENTITY, CHR_PUBLIC_IP         (form / detected)
     - WAN_IFACE                              (detected)
     - NODE_ROLES_SET                         (per-node enabled-roles set)

   Fleet-constant (identical in every render):
     - PANEL_WG_PUBKEY / PANEL_WG_HOST / PANEL_WG_PORT / PANEL_WG_ADDR
     - PROXY_WG_PUBKEY / PROXY_WG_HOST / PROXY_WG_PORT / PROXY_WG_ADDR
     - CHR_SHARED_SECRET (matches proxy's PROXY_CHR_SECRET; sec 6.5.1 note)
     - SSTP_CERT_NAME, IKE_CERT_NAME
     - CLIENT_SUPERNET, DNS_PUSH, GW_LOCAL_ADDR
     - IP_POOL_NAME, IP_POOL_RANGES         (shared client pool -- sec 6.5.2)
     - PPP_PROFILE_NAME                      (shared default PPP profile)
     - WG_USERS_PORT                         (user-WireGuard listener)
     - WG_USERS_ADDR                         (user-WG gateway address)
     - SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY               (e.g. "3m"; rollback window)

   See ``fleet/registry/script_render.py`` for the binding model and dataclass.

   IDEMPOTENCY (fix/fleet-script-idempotent):
     Every `add` in this script is preceded by `remove [find ...]` so the
     whole .rsc is safe to import twice in a row, or to re-import after a
     partial first run that already created some of the resources.

   SELF-LOCKOUT PROOF (feat/chr-unified-provisioning-complete):
     The owner runs this script on a CHR he is CONNECTED to. A broken
     firewall edit could lock him out mid-apply. RouterOS has no scripted
     ``safe-mode`` toggle that survives ``/import``, so we provision an
     explicit rollback guard:

       (a) ``/system backup save name="hobe-fleet-pre-apply"`` snapshots
           the prior working config;
       (b) ``/system scheduler add name="hobe-fleet-rollback"
           interval=SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY on-event="/system backup
           load ..."`` -- the rollback fires at T+delay UNLESS we cancel
           it;
       (c) the LAST line of the script removes the scheduler.

     Clean run => cancel executes, rollback never fires. Halted run
     (script error, lost connectivity, broken firewall) => scheduler
     trips at T+delay and restores the pre-apply backup. The window is
     documented in this header so the operator knows to wait before
     re-running.

   ROLE GATING (feat/chr-unified-provisioning-complete):
     ``NODE_ROLES_SET`` is the SET of roles enabled on this node (see
     app/services/node_roles.py -- empty list => all roles). The template
     conditionally enables service blocks per role:

       * ``radius_transport`` -- wg-data + RADIUS client + CoA listener;
       * ``vpn_sstp``         -- SSTP server (still gated on
                                ``SSTP_CERT_NAME`` being non-empty);
       * ``vpn_pptp``         -- PPTP server + GRE allow;
       * ``vpn_ipsec``        -- IKEv2 + L2TP/IPsec server (IKEv2 still
                                gated on ``IKE_CERT_NAME``);
       * ``vpn_wireguard``    -- wg-users user-WireGuard server.

     The firewall block emits the matching ``accept`` rules ONLY for
     roles that are enabled, so an unwanted port is never exposed.

   SURGICAL FIREWALL (feat/chr-unified-provisioning-complete):
     Owner brief: "I want everything surgical and strong; do not block anything that prevents legitimate connections". Block:

       1. ``hobe-fleet-fw-conntrack`` accept established,related,untracked
          -- first match for any existing flow including the SSH session
          carrying this very ``/import``;
       2. ``hobe-fleet-fw-invalid`` drop conntrack=invalid -- hygiene;
       3. ``hobe-fleet-fw-mgmt`` accept in=wg-mgmt src=PANEL_WG_ADDR/32 --
          panel-only management BEFORE any drop;
       4. ``hobe-fleet-fw-radius`` / ``-coa`` accept in=wg-data
          src=PROXY_WG_ADDR/32 (only when ``radius_transport`` enabled);
       5. wg-mgmt + wg-data UDP handshake accepts on the WAN iface;
       6. per-role VPN service accepts (sstp 443/tcp, pptp 1723/tcp +
          gre, ike 500,4500/udp + esp/50, l2tp 1701/udp, wg-users
          WG_USERS_PORT/udp) -- each labelled with its role so the
          remove-by-regex picks them up cleanly;
       7. ICMP accept with a rate limit;
       8. ``hobe-fleet-fw-no-public-radius`` drop udp 1812/1813/3799 on
          any iface OTHER than wg-data -- defence vs an operator who
          forgot to enable the role;
       9. ``hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last`` is the FINAL input rule -- every
          accept above explicit, then deny the rest.

     The explicit hoist-to-top of conntrack + mgmt + coa + radius via
     ``move destination=0`` survives stale operator drops the way the
     original sec 9b fix established. ``conntrack`` lands at absolute top so
     a re-import never breaks the very session running it.

   DNS-LESS BOOTSTRAP + :resolve OVERRIDE (fix/fleet-endpoint-resolve):
     A field finding: even with host-only endpoint-address,
     ``endpoint-address=proxy.hoberadius.com`` left wg-data with
     current-endpoint-address="" and no handshake -- replacing with the
     resolved IP literal worked instantly. The script now:
       (a) ensures /ip dns has at least one server (sets 1.1.1.1,8.8.8.8
           as fallback -- does NOT clobber an operator-set list);
       (b) tags each peer with a stable comment;
       (c) runs ``:resolve`` against PANEL_WG_HOST / PROXY_WG_HOST with
           up to 5 retries (2-second back-off) and overwrites the peer's
           endpoint-address with the resolved IP literal.
   ============================================================================ #}
{%- set ROLES = NODE_ROLES_SET|default(['radius_transport','vpn_sstp','vpn_pptp','vpn_ipsec','vpn_wireguard']) -%}
{%- set IP_POOL_NAME = IP_POOL_NAME|default('hobe-fleet-pool') -%}
{%- set IP_POOL_RANGES = IP_POOL_RANGES|default('10.50.0.10-10.50.255.254') -%}
{%- set PPP_PROFILE_NAME = PPP_PROFILE_NAME|default('hobe-fleet-default') -%}
{%- set WG_USERS_PORT = WG_USERS_PORT|default(51822) -%}
{%- set WG_USERS_ADDR = WG_USERS_ADDR|default('10.51.0.1/24') -%}
{%- set SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY = SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY|default('3m') -%}
# ============================================================
# HobeRadius unified CHR provisioning script  (v3, idempotent)
# Safe to re-import: every resource removes prior copies first.
# Self-lockout safe: arms a {{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }} rollback BEFORE
# touching anything; cancels it on clean completion. If you lose your
# session mid-apply, the CHR auto-reverts and you can re-run.
# ============================================================

/system identity set name="{{ ROUTER_IDENTITY }}"

# ============================================================
# 0a. SELF-LOCKOUT GUARD -- snapshot + auto-rollback
# ============================================================
# Take a backup of the CURRENT (working) config, then arm a one-shot
# scheduler that, in {{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }}, loads it back. The
# very last block of this script removes the scheduler. If anything
# below fails or breaks the admin session, the scheduler fires and the
# CHR boots into the snapshot, recovering the prior working state.
:do { /file remove [find name="hobe-fleet-pre-apply.backup"] } on-error={}
/system backup save name="hobe-fleet-pre-apply" dont-encrypt=yes
:delay 1s
/system scheduler
remove [find name="hobe-fleet-rollback"]
# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- the previous on-event used
#   /system backup load name=hobe-fleet-pre-apply
# which in scheduler context errors with: missing value(s) of
# argument(s) password (RouterOS 7.21.x requires the password arg
# even for an unencrypted backup) AND, because interval= makes the
# scheduler RECURRING, it fired every {{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }}
# FOREVER -- logging "rollback fired" + "executing script failed"
# ~20 times on chr-vpn-2 without ever restoring or self-removing.
#
# Redesign -- ONE-SHOT, valid, self-removing, bounded:
#   1. The on-event's FIRST action removes THIS scheduler, so it can
#      NEVER fire twice regardless of what follows (removing the
#      currently-running scheduler does not abort the running event).
#   2. The restore uses the correct non-interactive form
#      `password=""` (satisfies the required arg for the
#      dont-encrypt=yes backup).
#   3. The restore is wrapped in :do/on-error -- if backup load is
#      unsupported/erroring on this build, we log a precise actionable
#      reason and STOP (already self-removed). Break-glass access stays
#      active for manual recovery; we never loop.
add name="hobe-fleet-rollback" interval={{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }} \
    on-event=(":log warning \"hobe-fleet: rollback fired -- restoring pre-apply snapshot (one-shot)\"; /system scheduler remove [find name=hobe-fleet-rollback]; :do { /system backup load name=hobe-fleet-pre-apply password=\"\" } on-error={ :log error \"hobe-fleet: rollback restore FAILED -- backup load errored on this build. Scheduler already self-removed; NOT retrying. Break-glass access remains active for manual recovery.\" }") \
    policy=read,write,policy,test,password,sensitive \
    comment="hobe-fleet-rollback-guard (one-shot self-removing)"
:log info "hobe-fleet: rollback guard armed ({{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }} window, ONE-SHOT) -- script must run to completion to cancel it; if it fires it self-removes after one attempt"

# ---- 0b. DNS bootstrap (so :resolve works in section 2b) ----
# If the CHR has no DNS servers configured yet, set a public fallback.
# We DO NOT overwrite an operator-set DNS list.
:if ([:len [/ip dns get servers]] = 0) do={
    /ip dns set servers=1.1.1.1,8.8.8.8 allow-remote-requests=no
    :log info "hobe-fleet: bootstrapped /ip dns servers=1.1.1.1,8.8.8.8 (was empty)"
}

# ---- 1. WireGuard CONTROL tunnel (wg-mgmt) -----------------
# Control/telemetry ONLY. No default route, no NAT, no forwarding over this.
/interface wireguard peers
remove [find interface="wg-mgmt"]
/ip address
remove [find interface="wg-mgmt"]
/interface wireguard
remove [find name="wg-mgmt"]
add name=wg-mgmt listen-port=51820 private-key="{{ WG_MGMT_PRIVKEY }}"
/interface wireguard peers
{# endpoint-address MUST be host-only -- RouterOS rejects host:port silently
   and leaves current-endpoint-address="" with no handshake. The renderer
   splits the stored host:port into HOST + PORT bindings; see
   fleet.registry.script_render._split_endpoint. #}
add interface=wg-mgmt public-key="{{ PANEL_WG_PUBKEY }}" \
    endpoint-address={{ PANEL_WG_HOST }} endpoint-port={{ PANEL_WG_PORT }} \
    allowed-address={{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32 persistent-keepalive=25s \
    comment="hobe-fleet-mgmt"
/ip address
add interface=wg-mgmt address={{ WG_MGMT_ADDR }}     ;# e.g. 10.99.0.11/24 (shared mgmt net; /32 broke the return route)

{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
# ---- 2. WireGuard DATA path to RADIUS proxy (wg-data) ------
# Carries ONLY RADIUS 1812/1813 + CoA 3799 to the proxy. Role-gated on
# ``radius_transport``: nodes that are pure VPN terminators (no RADIUS
# transport) skip this block entirely.
/interface wireguard peers
remove [find interface="wg-data"]
/ip address
remove [find interface="wg-data"]
/interface wireguard
remove [find name="wg-data"]
add name=wg-data listen-port=51821 private-key="{{ WG_DATA_PRIVKEY }}"
/interface wireguard peers
{# Same as the wg-mgmt block -- host-only endpoint-address, port separate. #}
add interface=wg-data public-key="{{ PROXY_WG_PUBKEY }}" \
    endpoint-address={{ PROXY_WG_HOST }} endpoint-port={{ PROXY_WG_PORT }} \
    allowed-address={{ PROXY_WG_ADDR }}/32 persistent-keepalive=25s \
    comment="hobe-fleet-data"
/ip address
add interface=wg-data address={{ WG_DATA_ADDR }}     ;# e.g. 10.98.0.11/24 (shared data net; /32 broke the RADIUS return path)
{% else %}
# wg-data skipped: ``radius_transport`` role not enabled on this node.
# Pure VPN-terminator CHRs don't carry RADIUS to/from the proxy.
{% endif %}

# ---- 2b. Resolve peer hostnames -> set IP literal on each peer ----
# Field finding (fix/fleet-endpoint-resolve): RouterOS doesn't always
# resolve the peer host into a working endpoint at peer-add time.
# Retries 5x with 2s back-off.
#
# fix/fleet-wireguard-provisioning (BUG A): chr-vpn-2 came up with
# endpoint-address="" on BOTH peers even though :resolve succeeded in
# the log -- some build/path of RouterOS returned an empty string from
# the :do block AND the set still ran, overwriting the hostname the
# peer was added with. The fix: NEVER set endpoint-address to "". If
# the resolved value isn't a non-empty IP-shaped string, KEEP THE
# HOSTNAME that the peer was added with at peer-add time (the literal
# {{ PANEL_WG_HOST }} / {{ PROXY_WG_HOST }} -- RouterOS itself will
# keep re-resolving the hostname endpoint on each handshake retry).
:local hobeResolve do={
    :local host $1
    :for i from=1 to=5 do={
        :do {
            :local ip [:resolve $host]
            :log info ("hobe-fleet: resolved " . $host . " -> " . $ip . " (attempt " . $i . ")")
            :return $ip
        } on-error={
            :log warning ("hobe-fleet: :resolve " . $host . " failed (attempt " . $i . "/5)")
            :delay 2s
        }
    }
    :log error ("hobe-fleet: :resolve " . $host . " gave up after 5 attempts; leaving hostname on peer")
    :return ""
}

# hobeSetEndpoint: write endpoint-address ONLY when the resolved value
# is a non-empty IP-shaped string; on empty/garbage, leave whatever the
# peer-add set (the hostname) intact so the peer is NEVER left with
# endpoint-address="".
:local hobeSetEndpoint do={
    :local comm $1
    :local ip $2
    :local port $3
    :local fallback $4
    :local clean [:tostr $ip]
    :if ([:len $clean] > 0 && [:typeof [:find $clean "."]] != "nothing") do={
        /interface wireguard peers set [find comment=$comm] endpoint-address=$clean endpoint-port=$port
        :log info ("hobe-fleet: peer " . $comm . " endpoint-address set to literal " . $clean . ":" . $port)
    } else={
        # Keep / restore the hostname so RouterOS can re-resolve later.
        /interface wireguard peers set [find comment=$comm] endpoint-address=$fallback endpoint-port=$port
        :log warning ("hobe-fleet: peer " . $comm . " resolve unusable, keeping hostname " . $fallback . ":" . $port)
    }
}

:local panelIP [$hobeResolve "{{ PANEL_WG_HOST }}"]
$hobeSetEndpoint "hobe-fleet-mgmt" $panelIP {{ PANEL_WG_PORT }} "{{ PANEL_WG_HOST }}"
{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
:local proxyIP [$hobeResolve "{{ PROXY_WG_HOST }}"]
$hobeSetEndpoint "hobe-fleet-data" $proxyIP {{ PROXY_WG_PORT }} "{{ PROXY_WG_HOST }}"
{% endif %}

# ---- 2d. POST-SETUP ENDPOINT-ADDRESS VALIDATION ----
# fix/fleet-wireguard-provisioning (BUG A) - assert that each peer
# really carries a non-empty endpoint-address NOW. Empty = the resolve
# branch above misfired; we abort by leaving an error flag the rollback
# gate in section 12 will read (and refuse to cancel the rollback).
:global hobeWgValidationOk true
:global hobeWgValidationDetail ""
# fix/script-service-get-guard -- length-guard every wg peer find before
# get; if the peer creation step above misfired the find returns empty
# and the unguarded get halted the import with an invalid-internal-
# item-number error (RouterOS aborts even past a try/on-error here).
:local mgmtPeerRef [/interface wireguard peers find comment="hobe-fleet-mgmt"]
:local mgmtEp ""
:if ([:len $mgmtPeerRef] > 0) do={
    :set mgmtEp [/interface wireguard peers get $mgmtPeerRef endpoint-address]
}
:if ([:len [:tostr $mgmtEp]] = 0) do={
    :log error "hobe-fleet: BUG A - wg-mgmt peer endpoint-address is EMPTY after setup. No handshake will ever occur."
    :set hobeWgValidationOk false
    :set hobeWgValidationDetail "wg-mgmt endpoint-address empty"
} else={
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt endpoint-address OK = " . $mgmtEp)
}
{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
:local dataPeerRef [/interface wireguard peers find comment="hobe-fleet-data"]
:local dataEp ""
:if ([:len $dataPeerRef] > 0) do={
    :set dataEp [/interface wireguard peers get $dataPeerRef endpoint-address]
}
:if ([:len [:tostr $dataEp]] = 0) do={
    :log error "hobe-fleet: BUG A - wg-data peer endpoint-address is EMPTY after setup. No RADIUS will ever flow."
    :set hobeWgValidationOk false
    :set hobeWgValidationDetail ($hobeWgValidationDetail . " wg-data endpoint-address empty")
} else={
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-data endpoint-address OK = " . $dataEp)
}
{% endif %}

# ---- 2c. Key-identity audit trail ----
# Identity log lines: when a key mismatch produces a silent dead tunnel,
# /log carries the EXPECTED identities for one-glance comparison against
# "Settings -> Fleet Infrastructure" on the panel.
:log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt peer expects PANEL pubkey = {{ PANEL_WG_PUBKEY }}")
{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
:log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-data peer expects PROXY pubkey = {{ PROXY_WG_PUBKEY }}")
{% endif %}
# fix/script-service-get-guard -- length-guard the wg interface lookup
# before get; if the wg-mgmt interface creation step above misfired
# the find returns empty and the unguarded get halts the import.
:local hobeMgmtIf [/interface wireguard find name="wg-mgmt"]
:if ([:len $hobeMgmtIf] > 0) do={
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: this CHR wg-mgmt pubkey (give to panel) = " . [/interface wireguard get $hobeMgmtIf public-key])
} else={
    :log error "hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt interface MISSING after setup -- pubkey log skipped"
}
{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- SMOKING GUN #2: the script logged the
# wg-mgmt + wg-users pubkeys but NEVER the wg-DATA pubkey, so the
# operator had no way to confirm the proxy was given the right key to
# peer. The panel ALREADY persists this CHR's wg-data pubkey on the
# node row at mint time (it mints the keypair) and publishes it at
# GET /api/proxy/wg-peers with allowed-ips {{ WG_DATA_ADDR_IP }}/32 --
# but logging it on the CHR closes the diagnostic loop: the operator
# can eyeball that the on-CHR wg-data pubkey == the one the proxy must
# trust. Same length-guard pattern as wg-mgmt above.
:local hobeDataIf [/interface wireguard find name="wg-data"]
:if ([:len $hobeDataIf] > 0) do={
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: this CHR wg-data pubkey (proxy must peer this with allowed-ips {{ WG_DATA_ADDR_IP }}/32) = " . [/interface wireguard get $hobeDataIf public-key])
} else={
    :log error "hobe-fleet: wg-data interface MISSING after setup -- pubkey log skipped"
}
{% endif %}

{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
# ---- 3. RADIUS client -> the central proxy (FLEET-CONSTANT) -
# owner review fix #4 -- service=ppp ONLY (no `,login`). Allowing the
# `login` service would let RADIUS authenticate RouterOS admin login
# (ssh / winbox / WebFig). That widens the trust boundary: a compromised
# RADIUS server could grant router admin access, NOT just subscriber
# PPP auth. The panel manages router admins explicitly via /user; the
# proxy is for SUBSCRIBER PPP only.
/radius
remove [find comment="hobe-fleet-radius"]
add service=ppp address={{ PROXY_WG_ADDR }} secret="{{ CHR_SHARED_SECRET }}" \
    authentication-port=1812 accounting-port=1813 \
    src-address={{ WG_DATA_ADDR_IP }} timeout=3s \
    comment="hobe-fleet-radius"
# Force the entry to ENABLED on every (re-)import (X - DISABLED was seen on
# the first live install and silently killed RADIUS).
/radius enable [find comment="hobe-fleet-radius"]
/radius incoming
# Enable CoA / Disconnect listener so panel can kill/move sessions (RFC 5176)
set accept=yes port=3799

# Make PPP + login use RADIUS:
/ppp aaa
set use-radius=yes accounting=yes interim-update=5m
{% else %}
# RADIUS client skipped: ``radius_transport`` role not enabled.
# This node terminates VPNs locally (or only via the WireGuard mesh).
{% endif %}

# ---- 4. Shared IP pool + unified PPP profile (FLEET-CONSTANT) --
# sec 10.2 / sec 6.5.2: every node carries the SAME pool name + ranges + the
# SAME PPP profile (rate-limit driven by RADIUS Mikrotik-Rate-Limit).
# Subscriber roaming/failover keeps the same Framed-IP and the same
# profile across nodes => no disconnect.
#
# Idempotent: remove by stable comment/name-prefix, then re-add.
/ppp profile
remove [find comment="hobe-fleet-ppp"]
remove [find name="{{ PPP_PROFILE_NAME }}"]
/ip pool
remove [find name~"^hobe-fleet-pool"]
remove [find name="{{ IP_POOL_NAME }}"]
add name="{{ IP_POOL_NAME }}" ranges="{{ IP_POOL_RANGES }}" comment="hobe-fleet-pool"
/ppp profile
# IP allocation flow: prefer RADIUS Framed-IP (Access-Accept attribute);
# fall back to the shared pool by name. Same name + ranges on every node
# guarantees the framed IP is also valid post-roam.
add name="{{ PPP_PROFILE_NAME }}" local-address={{ GW_LOCAL_ADDR }} \
    remote-address="{{ IP_POOL_NAME }}" \
    use-encryption=required dns-server={{ DNS_PUSH }} \
    only-one=yes comment="hobe-fleet-ppp"
# Built-in default-encryption stays in sync as a safety mirror; CHR-level
# defaults (RouterOS pre-creates `default-encryption`) still need their
# remote-address to point at the shared pool so a tunnel that lands on
# the built-in profile still gets an IP.
set default-encryption local-address={{ GW_LOCAL_ADDR }} \
    remote-address="{{ IP_POOL_NAME }}" \
    use-encryption=required dns-server={{ DNS_PUSH }} \
    only-one=yes        ;# RADIUS Framed-IP wins when present

{% if 'vpn_pptp' in ROLES %}
# ---- 5. PPTP server (role: vpn_pptp) ----------------------
/interface pptp-server server
set enabled=yes authentication=mschap2 default-profile={{ PPP_PROFILE_NAME }} \
    keepalive-timeout=30
{% else %}
/interface pptp-server server
set enabled=no
# PPTP skipped: ``vpn_pptp`` role disabled on this node.
{% endif %}

{% if 'vpn_sstp' in ROLES %}
# ---- 6. SSTP server (role: vpn_sstp; TLS 443) ----------------
{# Cert-conditional: SSTP requires a TLS cert pre-imported on the CHR. We
   skip the whole sub-section when no cert name is configured on the panel
   -- emitting `certificate=` empty would fail with "input does not match
   any value of certificate". The "RADIUS link" SSTP for the customer NAS
   to dial in shares this same listener; both end-users AND the customer
   NAS authenticate via the RADIUS client above, distinguished by user. #}
{% if SSTP_CERT_NAME %}
/interface sstp-server server
set enabled=yes port=443 authentication=mschap2 \
    certificate={{ SSTP_CERT_NAME }} tls-version=only-1.2 \
    default-profile={{ PPP_PROFILE_NAME }} verify-client-certificate=no
{% else %}
# SSTP skipped: no TLS certificate configured on the panel yet.
# Set SSTP_CERT_NAME in /admin/fleet config (and pre-install the matching
# /certificate row on each CHR) to enable the SSTP server block here.
{% endif %}
{% else %}
/interface sstp-server server
set enabled=no
# SSTP skipped: ``vpn_sstp`` role disabled on this node.
{% endif %}

{% if 'vpn_ipsec' in ROLES %}
# ---- 7. IPsec / IKEv2 server (role: vpn_ipsec) -----------
# IPsec children reference parents by name -- clean child->parent order on
# remove, then parent->child on add.
/ip ipsec identity
remove [find peer="hobe-peer"]
/ip ipsec peer
remove [find name="hobe-peer"]
/ip ipsec mode-config
remove [find name="hobe-mc"]
/ip ipsec proposal
remove [find name="hobe-prop"]
/ip ipsec profile
remove [find name="hobe-ike"]
add name=hobe-ike dh-group=modp2048 enc-algorithm=aes-256 hash-algorithm=sha256
/ip ipsec proposal
add name=hobe-prop enc-algorithms=aes-256-cbc,aes-256-gcm pfs-group=modp2048
/ip ipsec mode-config
# Address ALSO via RADIUS for IKEv2 (no local pool); identity = vpn.hoberadius.com
add name=hobe-mc responder=yes
{% if IKE_CERT_NAME %}
/ip ipsec peer
add name=hobe-peer exchange-mode=ike2 profile=hobe-ike passive=yes
/ip ipsec identity
add auth-method=eap-radius generate-policy=port-strict mode-config=hobe-mc \
    peer=hobe-peer certificate={{ IKE_CERT_NAME }}
{% else %}
# IPsec IKEv2 identity + peer skipped: no IKEv2 certificate configured.
# Set IKE_CERT_NAME in /admin/fleet config to enable IKEv2.
{% endif %}

# ---- 7b. L2TP/IPsec server (role: vpn_ipsec) ----------------
# L2TP rides inside an IPsec transport. Enable L2TP and require the
# IPsec PSK so a plain-L2TP client can't reach us. The PSK is the same
# central CHR_SHARED_SECRET -- the panel is the SINGLE source of truth.
/interface l2tp-server server
set enabled=yes authentication=mschap2 default-profile={{ PPP_PROFILE_NAME }} \
    use-ipsec=required ipsec-secret="{{ CHR_SHARED_SECRET }}"
{% else %}
/ip ipsec identity
remove [find peer="hobe-peer"]
/ip ipsec peer
remove [find name="hobe-peer"]
/interface l2tp-server server
set enabled=no
# IPsec / L2TP skipped: ``vpn_ipsec`` role disabled on this node.
{% endif %}

{% if 'vpn_wireguard' in ROLES %}
# ---- 7c. WireGuard user server (role: vpn_wireguard) -------
# A dedicated wg interface for end-user clients. RouterOS auto-generates
# the private key on `add` (we deliberately do NOT pass private-key= so
# the device mints its own); the panel reads the matching public key
# back via the existing heartbeat/identity channel and distributes it to
# customer client devices when their tunnel is provisioned.
#
# Peers are added per-customer by a later panel call, NOT here -- this
# block only stands up the listener + gateway address. The firewall block
# below opens WG_USERS_PORT only when this role is enabled.
/interface wireguard peers
remove [find interface="wg-users"]
/ip address
remove [find interface="wg-users"]
/interface wireguard
remove [find name="wg-users"]
add name=wg-users listen-port={{ WG_USERS_PORT }} comment="hobe-fleet-users"
/ip address
add interface=wg-users address={{ WG_USERS_ADDR }} comment="hobe-fleet-users"
# fix/script-service-get-guard -- length-guard the wg interface lookup
# before get; if the wg-users add above misfired the find returns empty
# and the unguarded get halts the import.
:local hobeUsersIf [/interface wireguard find name="wg-users"]
:if ([:len $hobeUsersIf] > 0) do={
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-users public key (give to panel) = " . [/interface wireguard get $hobeUsersIf public-key])
} else={
    :log error "hobe-fleet: wg-users interface MISSING after setup -- pubkey log skipped"
}
{% else %}
/interface wireguard
remove [find name="wg-users"]
# wg-users skipped: ``vpn_wireguard`` role disabled on this node.
{% endif %}

# ---- 8. NAT / masquerade to the internet ------------------
# Client (RADIUS-assigned or pool-assigned) range egresses via this CHR's
# public IP.
/ip firewall nat
remove [find comment="hobe-fleet-nat-egress"]
add chain=srcnat action=masquerade out-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} \
    src-address={{ CLIENT_SUPERNET }} comment="hobe-fleet-nat-egress" ;# e.g. 10.0.0.0/8

# ============================================================
# 9. SURGICAL FIREWALL (input chain) -- clean rebuild, place-before order.
# ============================================================
# LIVE INCIDENT (fix/chr-hardening-safe-firewall-order -- chr-vpn-3):
#   A foreign rule `chain=input action=drop in-interface=ether1` (added
#   by an operator or older script) sat BEFORE our public WG/VPN allows
#   -> wg-mgmt handshake packets to UDP 51820 were dropped at the WAN
#   -> no wg-mgmt tunnel -> REST polls returned rest_failed -> wizard
#   stuck. The previous template used `add` then `move destination=0`
#   to hoist our allows to the top, but foreign drops interleaved
#   between the moves still beat us in first-match order.
#
# OWNER PRINCIPLE (clean-before-write): the script must clean anything
# before it writes to a location. Every section the script WRITES first
# REMOVES the conflicting prior state. For the INPUT chain on a
# dedicated fleet CHR (which we fully own) that means a CLEAN REBUILD:
# wipe every existing input rule and re-emit our authoritative ordered
# set. forward / output / nat chains are NOT touched beyond our own
# hobe-fleet-* tagged rules (see sec 8 nat / sec 9z below).
#
# Safety: the sec 0a 3-min self-lockout rollback is armed BEFORE this
# wipe runs, so a mid-rebuild session drop reverts to the prior
# working firewall.
#
# THE NEW APPROACH -- four guarantees:
#
#   1. CLEAN REBUILD of the INPUT chain only. `remove [find chain=input]`
#      wipes every existing input rule (ours + foreign + temp + duplicate),
#      then we re-emit our authoritative ordered set fresh. No risk of
#      stale operator rules surviving between adds.
#
#   2. Anchor `hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last` is added FIRST. Every other
#      rule is added with a place-before pointing at that anchor, so
#      the script's insertion order == the on-CHR effective top-to-
#      bottom order. No `move destination=0` games that fail on
#      interleaved foreign rules.
#
#   3. Re-running the script is BYTE-IDENTICAL output and converges to
#      the same effective order with zero duplicates (the input wipe
#      is total; the authoritative set is deterministic from bindings).
#
#   4. forward + output chains NOT touched. Only our tagged nat rule
#      in sec 8 is replaced (remove-by-comment, then add).
#
# Effective order on the CHR (top -> bottom):
#   conntrack accept            <- rule 0, first match
#   conntrack=invalid drop
#   wg-mgmt mgmt accept (PANEL)
#   wg-mgmt api-ssl 8443 accept (PANEL, if API user provisioned)
#   operator-IP ssh+winbox accept (if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS set)
#   wg-data RADIUS auth/acct accept (PROXY) -- if radius_transport role
#   wg-data CoA accept (PROXY) -- if radius_transport role
#   WAN wg-mgmt udp 51820 accept
#   WAN wg-data udp 51821 accept -- if radius_transport role
#   WAN VPN listener accepts (role-gated)
#   ICMP rate-limited accept
#   no-public-radius drop (1812/1813/3799 on non-wg-data ifaces)
#   drop-last                   <- rule N, final deny
#
# --- Step 1: CLEAN REBUILD -- wipe the input chain entirely ----------
/ip firewall filter
#
# Pre-wipe documentation sweeps. These remove statements are now
# REDUNDANT with the clean rebuild below -- `remove [find chain=input]`
# subsumes every comment-pattern remove. We keep them as:
#   (a) self-documenting INTENT -- names every bad shape this script
#       protects against (foreign broad drops, TEMP-labelled allows,
#       our own prior tagged rules);
#   (b) audit-log fidelity -- RouterOS logs the matched count per
#       remove, so a re-import shows exactly what patterns existed
#       before the clean rebuild swept them.
# A remove against an empty find is a no-op, so these are free.
remove [find comment~"^hobe-fleet-fw-"]
remove [find comment~"^TEMP allow"]
remove [find comment~"^TEMP-"]
remove [find comment~"^drop public input"]
# Broad foreign drops on in-interface=ether1 with no additional
# selectors -- these are the operator-added blanket drops that ended
# up above our allows on chr-vpn-3. We walk the matching rules and
# only remove the truly-broad ones (no protocol, no dst-port,
# no src-address). Logged for the post-import audit.
:foreach r in=[find chain=input action=drop in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }}] do={
    :local c [get $r comment]
    :local proto [/ip firewall filter get $r protocol]
    :local dport [/ip firewall filter get $r dst-port]
    :local src [/ip firewall filter get $r src-address]
    :if ([:typeof [:find $c "hobe-fleet-fw-"]] = "nothing" \
            && [:tostr $proto] = "" \
            && [:tostr $dport] = "" \
            && [:tostr $src] = "") do={
        :log warning ("hobe-fleet: removing foreign broad-public-drop rule comment=" . $c)
        remove $r
    }
}
#
# Total wipe of whatever survived. The sec 0a rollback scheduler armed
# BEFORE this line is the safety net: if anything below halts the
# script, the CHR reverts to the pre-apply snapshot at
# T+{{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }} and the prior firewall comes back.
#
# We log what we removed (count + the comment of each rule) before the
# wipe so the post-import audit log shows exactly what the script
# replaced -- useful when reviewing the diff between operator-edited
# state and the authoritative re-render.
:local wipedCount 0
:foreach r in=[find chain=input] do={
    :local c [/ip firewall filter get $r comment]
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: input-chain clean-rebuild -- removing rule comment=" . $c)
    :set wipedCount ($wipedCount + 1)
}
:if ($wipedCount > 0) do={
    :log warning ("hobe-fleet: input chain clean-rebuild -- " . $wipedCount . " prior rule(s) removed; re-emitting authoritative set")
}
remove [find chain=input]
# forward + output chains are NOT touched here. Our own tagged rules
# in those chains (currently none in the input chain rewrite -- see sec 8
# for nat) are managed by their own remove-by-comment blocks above.

# --- Step 2: drop-last anchor FIRST ---------------------------------
# Lands at the end of the table; every subsequent add uses a
# place-before pointing at this anchor, so the rule inserts JUST BEFORE
# drop-last and the previous insertion shifts up by one slot. Insertion
# order in the script == top-to-bottom order on the CHR. No `move`
# needed; foreign rules can't interleave.
add chain=input action=drop comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"

# --- Step 3: every accept + the no-public-radius drop, IN ORDER ----
# (A) Conntrack accept -- first match for established/related/untracked.
add chain=input action=accept connection-state=established,related,untracked \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    comment="hobe-fleet-fw-conntrack"

# (B) Drop conntrack=invalid early -- hygiene.
add chain=input action=drop connection-state=invalid \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    comment="hobe-fleet-fw-invalid"

# (C) Management accept -- wg-mgmt from PANEL/32. Keeps the live SSH
#     session over wg-mgmt alive across re-imports.
add chain=input in-interface=wg-mgmt src-address={{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32 \
    action=accept \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    comment="hobe-fleet-fw-mgmt"

{% if (API_USER|default('')) and (API_PASSWORD|default('')) %}
# (C') API REST 8443 accept -- wg-mgmt from PANEL/32 only. Was in sec 11
#      previously; consolidated here so the place-before anchor is
#      the only anchor anywhere in the script (no late re-anchoring).
add chain=input in-interface=wg-mgmt src-address={{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32 \
    protocol=tcp dst-port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }} \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-api-ssl"
{% endif %}

{% if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS|default('') %}
# (C") Operator manual-access -- WinBox + SSH from the owner's source
#      IP(s) on the WAN. This is the "I can still get into WinBox" rule:
#      WinBox/SSH remain reachable from those specific addresses even
#      after wg-mgmt is the primary management path. The list is
#      sanitised on the panel (CIDR-parsed, 0.0.0.0/0 rejected, capped
#      at 16 tokens) so we splice it verbatim into src-address=.
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} \
    src-address={{ OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS }} \
    protocol=tcp dst-port=22,8291 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-operator-admin"
{% endif %}

{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
# (D) RADIUS over wg-data -- auth/acct + CoA, scoped to the proxy IP.
add chain=input in-interface=wg-data src-address={{ PROXY_WG_ADDR }}/32 \
    protocol=udp dst-port=1812,1813 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-radius"
add chain=input in-interface=wg-data src-address={{ PROXY_WG_ADDR }}/32 \
    protocol=udp dst-port=3799 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-coa"
{% endif %}

# (E) Public WireGuard listener UDP on the WAN -- required for either
#     peer to handshake. THIS is the rule that the foreign broad drop
#     was beating on chr-vpn-3.
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=udp dst-port=51820 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-wg-mgmt-udp"
{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=udp dst-port=51821 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-wg-data-udp"
{% endif %}

# (F) Role-gated public VPN service ports.
{% if 'vpn_sstp' in ROLES and SSTP_CERT_NAME %}
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=tcp dst-port=443 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-sstp"
{% endif %}
{% if 'vpn_pptp' in ROLES %}
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=tcp dst-port=1723 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-pptp-ctrl"
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=gre \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-pptp-data"
{% endif %}
{% if 'vpn_ipsec' in ROLES %}
# owner review fix #3 -- IKE 500/4500 firewall accept is no longer
# gated on IKE_CERT_NAME. The cert gates the IKEv2 SERVER (sec7), not
# the WAN-side firewall accept; if vpn_ipsec is enabled but the cert
# isn't ready yet, we still want UDP 500/4500 + ESP + UDP 1701 to be
# permitted at the firewall layer so the operator's NAT-T / IKE
# negotiations don't get blackholed once the cert lands.
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=udp dst-port=500,4500 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-ike"
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=ipsec-esp \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-esp"
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=udp dst-port=1701 \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-l2tp"
{% endif %}
{% if 'vpn_wireguard' in ROLES %}
add chain=input in-interface={{ WAN_IFACE }} protocol=udp dst-port={{ WG_USERS_PORT }} \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    action=accept comment="hobe-fleet-fw-wg-users"
{% endif %}

# (G) Sane ICMP -- pings work but can't flood.
add chain=input protocol=icmp action=accept limit=50,5:packet \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    comment="hobe-fleet-fw-icmp"

# (H) Defence vs an operator that forgot the role flag -- public RADIUS
#     ports must NEVER answer outside wg-data.
add chain=input protocol=udp dst-port=1812,1813,3799 action=drop \
    place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
    comment="hobe-fleet-fw-no-public-radius"

# ---- 10. control-plane is NOT a data route ----------------
# Ensure wg-mgmt carries no default route / no forwarding (invariant).
/ip route
# (no default via wg-mgmt -- intentionally absent)

# ---- 11. Panel-side read-only API user (live-metrics poller) ----
# A dedicated RouterOS user the panel logs in as to read CPU, /ppp/active
# count and interface bytes -- over the REST API on www-ssl ONLY, exposed
# on the wg-mgmt source (NEVER the WAN). The collector at
# app/services/routeros_client.py speaks HTTPS REST against
# https://<host>:<port>/rest/, so the matching service is `www-ssl`.
#
# Three live-incident fixes baked into this block (fix/fleet-metrics-wire-bugs):
#   1. PROTOCOL: www-ssl (REST), not api-ssl (binary).
#   2. CERTIFICATE: cert assigned so the TCP listener actually binds.
#   3. ACL DIRECTION: source-IP ACL points at the PANEL's wg-mgmt IP,
#      not the CHR's own -- so the panel itself isn't blocked.
{% if (API_USER|default('')) and (API_PASSWORD|default('')) %}
# feat/chr-auto-scoped-mgmt-user -- dedicated SCOPED management user.
#
# The owner's idea (paraphrased): instead of waiting for me to set
# admin or hobe-panel manually, the script should auto-create a
# unified management user with the exact privileges per need. So
# the script ALWAYS provisions a dedicated user bound to a
# DEDICATED group with the EXACT policy set the panel needs -- never the
# default ``read`` / ``full`` / ``write`` groups, never a built-in
# RouterOS user. Renderer auto-mints user+password if no operator
# override was set; reserved built-in names (admin/root/support/
# operator) are substituted to HARD_DEFAULT_USER upstream so this
# block never has to clobber a built-in row.
#
# Policy set -- see fleet/registry/onboarding_service.py for the audit
# of every REST call the panel actually makes. Granted:
#
#   read        -- system/resource, /interface, /ppp/active, etc.
#   write       -- PUT/PATCH on /ppp/{secret,profile}, /ip/pool, /ip/ipsec/*,
#                 /interface/wireguard{,/peers}
#   sensitive   -- required to write ppp/secret password=, ipsec PSK,
#                 wireguard peer private-key=
#   reboot      -- /system/reboot from the CHR console "(reboot)"
#   rest-api    -- login via REST API (the only login channel the panel
#                 uses; the unified script disables SSH/WinBox/FTP/web/
#                 telnet for this user at the /ip service layer too)
#
# DENIED by omission (RouterOS rule): api (binary), ssh, winbox, ftp,
# web, telnet, password (no user-mgmt), policy (no /system/scripts),
# sniff, test, romon, dude, tikapp, local -- everything NOT in the
# granted list above stays denied. If a future panel call needs a new
# policy, justify it in the renderer's audit + add it to the granted
# list below.
#
# LIVE INCIDENT (fix/chr-group-policy-granted-only -- chr-vpn-3,
# WinBox 4.1):
#   Script Error: input does not match any value of policy
#   (/user/group/add (policy); line 391)
# Root cause: RouterOS v7 `/user group add policy=` accepts a
# comma-separated list of GRANTED policy names ONLY. `!negation`
# tokens (e.g. `!ssh`) are NOT valid input -- RouterOS denies any
# UNLISTED policy by default, so deny-by-omission is the only
# correct form. The previous policy carried `!api,!ssh,...,!tikapp`
# and the parser errored on the first `!` token, leaving the group
# unprovisioned -> /user add referenced a non-existent group ->
# import halted. Fix: granted-only tokens.
# LIVE INCIDENT (fix/chr-group-idempotent-no-remove -- chr-vpn-3):
#   Script Error: failure: group has some users (/user/group/remove)
# Root cause: ``/user group remove`` REFUSES to delete a group that
# still has members. On a fresh install the group has no users so
# remove succeeds; on every RE-IMPORT the group already carries
# ``hobe-panel`` (added later in this same block on the previous
# run), so the remove fails and the import halts.
#
# Fix: ADD-OR-SET. If the group is absent we ``add`` it; if it's
# present we ``set`` it to the same policy + comment. ``set`` does
# not need the group to be empty, so re-imports work without ever
# removing a populated row.
/user group
:if ([:len [/user group find name="{{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}"]] = 0) do={
    /user group add name="{{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}" \
        policy=read,write,sensitive,reboot,rest-api \
        comment="hobe-fleet: scoped panel management user group (granted-only; everything else denied by omission)"
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: created scoped user group {{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}")
} else={
    /user group set [find name="{{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}"] \
        policy=read,write,sensitive,reboot,rest-api \
        comment="hobe-fleet: scoped panel management user group (granted-only; everything else denied by omission)"
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: refreshed policy on existing scoped group {{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}")
}

# User row -- ADD-OR-SET, no remove. On first install the row is
# absent; on every re-import it already exists in the scoped group.
#
# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- SMOKING GUN #3: the SET branch used
# to refresh group + comment but DELIBERATELY NOT password=, on the
# theory that "the first /user add already pinned it". That theory is
# WRONG and was the cause of the live 'login failure for user
# hobe-panel via api' (RouterOS logs REST auth failures as via-api):
#   * the user row can pre-exist from an EARLIER import that baked a
#     DIFFERENT generated password, OR the panel rotated the stored
#     secret -- and the SET branch then left the CHR password STALE,
#     diverging from what the panel dials with over REST www-ssl:8443.
# The panel is the single source of truth (panel-mints-panel-knows) so
# the script MUST converge the CHR password to {{ API_USER }}'s
# panel-known secret on EVERY import. We therefore set password= in
# BOTH branches. This guarantees:
#   CHR hobe-panel password == panel-stored secret == panel REST creds.
#
# Find-by-comment guard: we only manage our OWN row (the
# ``hobe-fleet-api-managed`` comment). A built-in row at the same
# name (admin/root/...) is untouched -- the renderer substitutes
# reserved names off API_USER upstream so the second branch
# below is belt-and-braces only.
/user
:if ([:len [/user find name="{{ API_USER }}"]] = 0) do={
    /user add name="{{ API_USER }}" \
        group="{{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}" \
        password="{{ API_PASSWORD }}" \
        comment="hobe-fleet-api-managed"
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: created user {{ API_USER }} in scoped group {{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }} (password set to panel secret)")
} else={
    :if ([:len [/user find name="{{ API_USER }}" comment="hobe-fleet-api-managed"]] > 0) do={
        /user set [find name="{{ API_USER }}" comment="hobe-fleet-api-managed"] \
            group="{{ API_GROUP|default('hobe-fleet-mgmt') }}" \
            password="{{ API_PASSWORD }}" \
            comment="hobe-fleet-api-managed"
        :log info ("hobe-fleet: refreshed managed user {{ API_USER }} -- group + password re-converged to panel secret (fixes REST via-api login failure on stale password)")
    } else={
        :log warning ("hobe-fleet: user {{ API_USER }} exists and is NOT our managed row -- refusing to clobber it. Pick a non-conflicting username from the panel's "Settings -> Fleet Infrastructure" page; auto-provisioned defaults already avoid every RouterOS built-in.")
    }
}

# Self-signed PKI for www-ssl: a tiny local CA + a leaf signed by it.
#
# LIVE INCIDENT (fix/chr-unified-wg-mgmt-key-bootstrap):
# 2s delay between sign + service-assign was too short on slower CHRs
# (1-vCPU contabo VPS under sec 0a-backup + sec 9-firewall CPU load).
# ``/ip service set www-ssl certificate=hobe-fleet-api-cert`` fired
# while the cert was still being signed -> set errored silently -> www-ssl
# stayed DISABLED -> panel TCP to :8443 was refused -> connect_failed ->
# wg_verify reported rest_failed -> wizard stuck.
#
# Fix: bumped each delay 2s -> 5s AND added an explicit poll-wait that
# checks the cert's ``invalid-after`` field (signed certs carry an
# expiry; unsigned ones don't). The :for retries 10 x 1s before
# giving up + logging -- even on a saturated CHR the cert is ready
# within 10 s.
/certificate
remove [find name="hobe-fleet-api-cert"]
remove [find name="hobe-fleet-ca"]
add name=hobe-fleet-ca common-name=hobe-fleet-ca \
    days-valid=3650 key-usage=key-cert-sign,crl-sign
sign hobe-fleet-ca
:delay 5s
/certificate
add name=hobe-fleet-api-cert common-name=hobe-fleet-api \
    days-valid=3650 key-usage=digital-signature,key-encipherment,tls-server
sign hobe-fleet-api-cert ca=hobe-fleet-ca
:delay 5s

# Poll-wait: ensure the leaf cert is fully signed (has invalid-after)
# before we assign it to www-ssl. The set-line that follows errors
# silently when the cert isn't ready yet, leaving www-ssl disabled --
# the on-CHR cause of `connect_failed` on slow CHRs.
#
# LIVE INCIDENT (fix/chr-script-remove-break -- chr-vpn-3):
#   Script Error: bad command name break (line 469 column 28)
# Root cause: `:break` inside a nested ``:if do={}`` is rejected by
# RouterOS ("bad command name break"). The construct is unreliable
# across v7 builds and we deliberately do NOT rely on it.
#
# BREAK-FREE pattern: the loop ALWAYS runs all 15 iterations, but
# each iteration's body is gated by ``!$certReady`` -- once the cert
# is ready the body and the ``:delay 1s`` are skipped, so the loop
# spins through the remaining counter ticks with effectively no
# work. Worst-case overshoot: 14 noop ticks (~= a few us each). No
# `:break`, no `:continue` -- pure flag-gated iteration.
:local certReady false
:for i from=1 to=15 do={
    :if (!$certReady) do={
        :do {
            :local cert [/certificate find name="hobe-fleet-api-cert"]
            :if ([:len $cert] > 0) do={
                :local exp [/certificate get $cert invalid-after]
                :if ([:typeof $exp] != "nothing" && [:tostr $exp] != "") do={
                    :set certReady true
                }
            }
        } on-error={}
        :if (!$certReady) do={ :delay 1s }
    }
}
:if ($certReady = false) do={
    :log error "hobe-fleet: hobe-fleet-api-cert not ready after 15s -- www-ssl will NOT bind on this run; re-run /import to retry."
}

# www-ssl = REST API over HTTPS. address= is the SOURCE-IP ACL --
# restrict to the PANEL's wg-mgmt IP (PANEL_WG_ADDR/32). This is safe
# to set unconditionally because the panel ALWAYS dials from
# PANEL_WG_ADDR over wg-mgmt; restricting at the service layer is a
# defence-in-depth complement to the sec 9 firewall rule.
/ip service
set www-ssl disabled=no port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }} \
    certificate=hobe-fleet-api-cert address={{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32
set api     disabled=yes  ;# binary API stays off (we use REST)
set api-ssl disabled=yes  ;# binary-over-TLS stays off (we use REST/www-ssl)
set www     disabled=yes  ;# plain HTTP stays off
set telnet  disabled=yes
set ftp     disabled=yes

# --- WG-MGMT-FIRST SAFETY GATE + MANUAL-ACCESS UNION ----------------
# Hardened ssh/winbox source-IP ACL = the UNION of:
#   * the panel over wg-mgmt:   PANEL_WG_ADDR/32        (always)
#   * the owner's source IPs:   OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS      (if set)
#
# That way WinBox is NEVER fully blocked: the owner can manage from
# his own IP even when wg-mgmt is down. NEVER 0.0.0.0/0 -- the panel
# validator rejects it.
#
# We still verify wg-mgmt is REACHABLE before applying the restriction.
# Two cases:
#
#   (a) wg-mgmt reachable -> apply the union ACL on ssh + winbox.
#       This is the secure final state.
#
#   (b) wg-mgmt unreachable (panel hasn't added this CHR as a wg-mgmt
#       peer yet) ->
#         - if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS is SET: still apply the union, so the
#           owner reaches WinBox/SSH from his own IP while the panel
#           side is fixed. No temp-emergency rule needed (the operator
#           accept rule emitted in sec 9 handles it).
#         - if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS is UNSET: keep ssh/winbox listening
#           on default + add a comment-tagged TEMP emergency-admin
#           firewall rule (cleaned on next clean run). Warn the
#           operator + tell him the break-glass path (provider VPS
#           console -> /system script run hobe-open-winbox -- see sec 11b).
#
# The 3-min self-lockout rollback scheduler armed in sec 0a is the second
# safety net underneath this gate -- a verify false-positive that cuts
# the session still recovers.

# Compose the address ACL. RouterOS /ip service accepts a comma-
# separated address list -- we splice PANEL/32 with the operator IPs.
{% if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS|default('') %}
:local mgmtAddrACL "{{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32,{{ OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS }}"
{% else %}
:local mgmtAddrACL "{{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32"
{% endif %}

:local mgmtReachable false
:do {
    :local pres [/ping address={{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }} interface=wg-mgmt count=3 as-value]
    :if ([:typeof $pres] = "array") do={
        :foreach p in=$pres do={
            :if ([:typeof $p] = "array") do={
                :if ([:typeof ($p->"received")] != "nothing") do={
                    :if (($p->"received") > 0) do={ :set mgmtReachable true }
                }
            }
        }
    }
} on-error={}

{% if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS|default('') %}
# OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS is set -> always apply the union ACL, regardless of
# wg-mgmt state. WinBox stays reachable from the owner's IP either way.
/ip service set ssh    address=$mgmtAddrACL disabled=no
/ip service set winbox address=$mgmtAddrACL disabled=no
:if ($mgmtReachable) do={
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt reachable; ssh+winbox ACL = " . $mgmtAddrACL)
} else={
    :log warning ("hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt NOT reachable yet, but operator-IP allow is set; ssh+winbox ACL = " . $mgmtAddrACL . " -- WinBox remains reachable from those sources.")
}
{% else %}
# OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS is NOT set -> run the original verify-then-restrict
# flow. On wg-mgmt failure keep ssh/winbox open + add a temp emergency
# rule + warn the operator (with break-glass instructions).
:if ($mgmtReachable) do={
    /ip service set ssh    address=$mgmtAddrACL disabled=no
    /ip service set winbox address=$mgmtAddrACL disabled=no
    :log info ("hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt verified reachable -- ssh+winbox restricted to " . $mgmtAddrACL)
} else={
    # owner review fix #1 -- BOTH layers must agree, otherwise the
    # temp firewall accept is silently dropped by the service ACL.
    # OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS is unset AND wg-mgmt is down: open ssh/winbox
    # at the SERVICE layer too (0.0.0.0/0) so the panel-recovery path
    # actually works. The 3-min self-lockout rollback armed in sec0a
    # is the safety net that bounds the exposure window if this apply
    # halted mid-way; otherwise the operator is expected to either
    # (a) fix wg-mgmt and re-import, OR (b) set OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS on
    # the panel and re-export, both of which re-restrict at the next
    # apply.
    /ip service set ssh    address=0.0.0.0/0 disabled=no
    /ip service set winbox address=0.0.0.0/0 disabled=no
    /ip firewall filter
    :if ([:len [find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-temp-emergency-admin"]] = 0) do={
        add chain=input action=accept protocol=tcp dst-port=22,8291 \
            place-before=[find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"] \
            comment="hobe-fleet-fw-temp-emergency-admin"
    }
    :log warning "hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt NOT reachable from this CHR -- ssh/winbox service ACL 0.0.0.0/0 + emergency-admin firewall accept tcp/22,8291 active. Either (a) set OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS on the panel and re-export, or (b) fix wg-mgmt and re-import; both re-restrict on next apply. Recovery: VPS provider console -> /system script run hobe-open-winbox (opens WinBox for 15m)."
    :put "WARNING hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt NOT reachable yet. ssh/winbox service ACL 0.0.0.0/0 + emergency-admin firewall accept tcp/22,8291 active. Recovery break-glass: VPS console -> /system script run hobe-open-winbox"
}
{% endif %}

# -- operator-facing summary print -----------------------------------
{% if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS|default('') %}
:log warning ("hobe-fleet: Management ACL applied -- ssh/winbox accept from PANEL/32 + OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS=" . "{{ OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS }}" . ". Public WinBox/SSH from any other source is BLOCKED.")
:put ("hobe-fleet: ssh+winbox ACL = PANEL_WG_ADDR/32 + OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS (" . "{{ OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS }}" . "). Break-glass: VPS console -> /system script run hobe-open-winbox (15 min open WinBox, auto-close).")
{% else %}
:log warning "hobe-fleet: Management services are restricted to wg-mgmt {{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32 only (OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS not set). Public WinBox/SSH and public WebFig will NOT work after hardening -- public WebFig is NOT supported (www-ssl is bound to {{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32). Break-glass: VPS console -> /system script run hobe-open-winbox (15 min auto-close) or hobe-open-webfig (15 min auto-close)."
:put "hobe-fleet WARNING: ssh+winbox restricted to wg-mgmt {{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32; public WebFig is NOT supported. Break-glass: VPS console -> /system script run hobe-open-winbox (or hobe-open-webfig)"
{% endif %}
{% else %}
# Live-metrics API user skipped: API_USER and/or API_PASSWORD not set on
# the panel. The dashboard will keep showing "no measurements yet" for CPU /
# sessions / bandwidth until the operator configures these in
# "Settings -> Fleet Infrastructure -> metrics read credentials".
{% endif %}

# CHR_PUBLIC_IP for this node (egress identity, documented for ops): {{ CHR_PUBLIC_IP }}

# ============================================================
# 11b. BREAK-GLASS MANUAL ACCESS -- provider-console recovery scripts
# ============================================================
# Owner: "There must be a manual WinBox entry path". There must always
# be a guaranteed manual recovery path that the network firewall can
# NEVER block -- because the recovery is initiated from the VPS
# provider's console (Hetzner / NovoServe VNC / Serial) which is a
# console session on the VM, not an IP session. That session bypasses
# /ip firewall filter entirely; it talks to the RouterOS shell
# directly. From that shell the operator runs:
#
#     /system script run hobe-open-winbox
#
# ...and WinBox opens for 15 minutes (then auto-reverts to the hardened
# state). For an explicit close: /system script run hobe-close-winbox.
#
# Idempotency: scripts are managed ADD-OR-SET by name (same pattern
# as /user group in sec 11). Clean-before-write -- if the row exists we
# overwrite its source; if not we add it. Re-imports converge.
#
# Why this is safe:
#   * The script source is the SCRIPT'S WORK -- it widens winbox only
#     TEMPORARILY (15 min) and schedules its own revert. If the
#     operator forgets, the scheduler re-tightens automatically.
#   * The scripts are bound to the panel's mgmt group
#     (`hobe-fleet-mgmt`) -- only a logged-in admin can run them.
#   * Running them is an EXPLICIT operator action; nothing on the
#     CHR triggers them on its own.
#
# Visible to the operator via /system script print (also shown in
# the sec 13 validation dump).
{# fix/chr-script-syntax-355 -- single-line source bodies.

   RouterOS lesson learned from chr-vpn-2 import: `\n\` inside a quoted
   `source="..."` is NOT a "newline + line-continuation" pair --
   backslash-at-EOL is RouterOS line continuation OUTSIDE strings only.
   Inside a quoted string the trailing `\` followed by a real newline
   is invalid and trips the parser. Same goes for arithmetic in
   scheduler `interval=` -- it wants a literal time, not `($x . "m")`.

   Robust shape (this is what's now emitted):
     source="cmd1; cmd2; cmd3; ..."
   one logical line, `;` separates statements, no embedded newlines,
   no leading-underscore locals, literal `interval=15m`.
#}
{% if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS|default('') -%}
{%- set closeACL = PANEL_WG_ADDR ~ '/32,' ~ OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set closeACL = PANEL_WG_ADDR ~ '/32' -%}
{%- endif %}
/system script
# fix/fleet-wireguard-provisioning (BUG G) - CLOSE-FIRST ORDERING.
# Pre-fix the open-* scripts armed `hobe-close-winbox-auto` that called
# `/system script run hobe-close-winbox`. On the FIRST import the close
# script didn't exist yet when the open block ran -- the operator's
# manual `run hobe-open-winbox` would widen the surface AND schedule a
# call to a script RouterOS doesn't have yet, so the scheduler tick
# would log "no such script" and the public surface would stay open
# indefinitely. Defining close-* BEFORE open-* removes the race entirely.
#
# -- (1) hobe-close-winbox -- immediate re-restrict to hardened state --
# Body (single line, `;` separated):
#   1. log + put the operator-facing notice
#   2. restore ssh + winbox /ip service ACL to the hardened union
#      (PANEL_WG_ADDR/32 plus OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS if set -- baked at
#      render time so this script needs no panel round-trip)
#   3. remove the break-glass firewall rule + the auto-revert scheduler
:if ([:len [find name="hobe-close-winbox"]] = 0) do={
    add name="hobe-close-winbox" \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing WinBox; restoring hardened ACL\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing WinBox; restoring hardened ACL\"; /ip service set winbox address=\"{{ closeACL }}\" disabled=no; /ip service set ssh address=\"{{ closeACL }}\" disabled=no; /ip firewall filter; :do { remove [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass\"] } on-error={}; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-winbox-auto\"] } on-error={}; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: hardened ACL restored\""
} else={
    set [find name="hobe-close-winbox"] \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing WinBox; restoring hardened ACL\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing WinBox; restoring hardened ACL\"; /ip service set winbox address=\"{{ closeACL }}\" disabled=no; /ip service set ssh address=\"{{ closeACL }}\" disabled=no; /ip firewall filter; :do { remove [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass\"] } on-error={}; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-winbox-auto\"] } on-error={}; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: hardened ACL restored\""
}

# -- (2) hobe-open-winbox -- temporarily widen WinBox for recovery --
# Body (single line, `;` separated):
#   1. log + put the operator-facing notice
#   2. widen ssh + winbox /ip service ACL to 0.0.0.0/0
#   3. add a tagged firewall accept for tcp:22,8291 above drop-last
#      (only if not already present -- idempotent)
#   4. remove any stale auto-revert scheduler, then arm a fresh one
#      with interval=15m calling hobe-close-winbox on tick. This is
#      safe ONLY because hobe-close-winbox above was created FIRST.
:if ([:len [find name="hobe-open-winbox"]] = 0) do={
    add name="hobe-open-winbox" \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening WinBox for 15 minutes\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening WinBox for 15 minutes\"; /ip service set winbox address=\"0.0.0.0/0\" disabled=no; /ip service set ssh address=\"0.0.0.0/0\" disabled=no; /ip firewall filter; :if ([:len [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass\"]] = 0) do={ add chain=input action=accept protocol=tcp dst-port=22,8291 place-before=[find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last\"] comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass\" }; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-winbox-auto\"] } on-error={}; add name=\"hobe-close-winbox-auto\" interval=15m on-event=\"/system script run hobe-close-winbox\" comment=\"hobe-fleet-break-glass\"; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: auto-revert in 15m via hobe-close-winbox-auto\""
} else={
    set [find name="hobe-open-winbox"] \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening WinBox for 15 minutes\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening WinBox for 15 minutes\"; /ip service set winbox address=\"0.0.0.0/0\" disabled=no; /ip service set ssh address=\"0.0.0.0/0\" disabled=no; /ip firewall filter; :if ([:len [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass\"]] = 0) do={ add chain=input action=accept protocol=tcp dst-port=22,8291 place-before=[find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last\"] comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass\" }; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-winbox-auto\"] } on-error={}; add name=\"hobe-close-winbox-auto\" interval=15m on-event=\"/system script run hobe-close-winbox\" comment=\"hobe-fleet-break-glass\"; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: auto-revert in 15m via hobe-close-winbox-auto\""
}

# -- (3) hobe-close-webfig -- restore www-ssl to PANEL_WG_ADDR/32 --
# fix/fleet-wireguard-provisioning (BUG G) - define CLOSE before OPEN
# so the auto-revert scheduler that the open block arms always has a
# real script name to run on the first tick.
# Mirrors hobe-close-winbox: restore the hardened ACL on www-ssl,
# remove the break-glass firewall rule + the auto-revert scheduler.
:if ([:len [find name="hobe-close-webfig"]] = 0) do={
    add name="hobe-close-webfig" \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing public WebFig; restoring hardened www-ssl ACL\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing WebFig; restoring www-ssl ACL to {{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32\"; /ip service set www-ssl address=\"{{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32\" disabled=no port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }}; /ip firewall filter; :do { remove [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass-webfig\"] } on-error={}; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-webfig-auto\"] } on-error={}; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: WebFig hardened state restored\""
} else={
    set [find name="hobe-close-webfig"] \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing public WebFig; restoring hardened www-ssl ACL\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: closing WebFig; restoring www-ssl ACL to {{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32\"; /ip service set www-ssl address=\"{{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}/32\" disabled=no port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }}; /ip firewall filter; :do { remove [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass-webfig\"] } on-error={}; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-webfig-auto\"] } on-error={}; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: WebFig hardened state restored\""
}

# -- (4) hobe-open-webfig -- temporarily widen public WebFig (HTTPS) --
# Owner review #2: after hardening, public WebFig is NOT supported
# (www disabled, www-ssl restricted to PANEL_WG_ADDR/32). The
# production path is wg-mgmt REST (the panel) or the WinBox break-
# glass above. This script is the optional WebFig recovery for the
# rare case where the operator NEEDS the HTML5 UI from the public
# WAN (e.g. WinBox is broken on his machine and he doesn't have
# wg-mgmt up). It widens /ip service www-ssl to 0.0.0.0/0 on port
# 8443 + opens tcp/8443 above drop-last + arms an auto-close timer
# that fires hobe-close-webfig in 15 minutes (safe ONLY because the
# close-webfig script above was defined FIRST -- BUG G).
#
# REASON to PREFER WinBox: the WebFig path is HTTPS to the wg-mgmt
# certificate (hobe-fleet-api-cert) which is self-signed -- browsers
# block by default. WinBox doesn't have that issue.
:if ([:len [find name="hobe-open-webfig"]] = 0) do={
    add name="hobe-open-webfig" \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening public WebFig for 15 minutes\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening public WebFig for 15 minutes (HTTPS port 8443, self-signed cert -- browser will warn)\"; /ip service set www-ssl address=\"0.0.0.0/0\" disabled=no port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }}; /ip firewall filter; :if ([:len [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass-webfig\"]] = 0) do={ add chain=input action=accept protocol=tcp dst-port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }} place-before=[find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last\"] comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass-webfig\" }; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-webfig-auto\"] } on-error={}; add name=\"hobe-close-webfig-auto\" interval=15m on-event=\"/system script run hobe-close-webfig\" comment=\"hobe-fleet-break-glass\"; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: WebFig auto-revert in 15m via hobe-close-webfig-auto\""
} else={
    set [find name="hobe-open-webfig"] \
        comment="hobe-fleet-break-glass" \
        policy=read,write,policy,test,reboot,sensitive \
        source=":log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening public WebFig for 15 minutes\"; :put \"hobe-fleet break-glass: opening public WebFig for 15 minutes (HTTPS port 8443, self-signed cert -- browser will warn)\"; /ip service set www-ssl address=\"0.0.0.0/0\" disabled=no port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }}; /ip firewall filter; :if ([:len [find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass-webfig\"]] = 0) do={ add chain=input action=accept protocol=tcp dst-port={{ API_PORT|default(8443) }} place-before=[find comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last\"] comment=\"hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass-webfig\" }; /system scheduler; :do { remove [find name=\"hobe-close-webfig-auto\"] } on-error={}; add name=\"hobe-close-webfig-auto\" interval=15m on-event=\"/system script run hobe-close-webfig\" comment=\"hobe-fleet-break-glass\"; :log warning \"hobe-fleet break-glass: WebFig auto-revert in 15m via hobe-close-webfig-auto\""
}

:log info "hobe-fleet: break-glass scripts provisioned (hobe-open-winbox / hobe-close-winbox / hobe-open-webfig / hobe-close-webfig). Run from VPS provider console if locked out."

# ============================================================
# 12. ROLLBACK VALIDATION GATE -- 12 explicit checks before CANCEL
# ============================================================
# fix/fleet-wireguard-provisioning (BUG F) -- pre-fix, the rollback
# scheduler was cancelled UNCONDITIONALLY at the end of the script
# (any time the parser reached this line). That hid the chr-vpn-2
# class of failure: the script ran end-to-end, but wg-mgmt never
# handshook (empty endpoint, wrong key, missing server peer) so the
# CHR was permanently unreachable -- yet the rollback was cancelled
# so the (broken) firewall stayed. The 3-min revert window's whole
# point is to UNDO an apply that broke connectivity; cancelling on
# "I reached the bottom of the file" defeats it.
#
# The gate below cancels ONLY when EVERY listed check passes. Any
# failure leaves :global hobeRollbackOk false; the cancel block is
# skipped and the rollback fires at T+{{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }}.
:global hobeRollbackOk true
:global hobeRollbackReason ""
# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- CLASSIFICATION SPLIT.
#
# The rollback exists to UNDO a LOCAL break that locks the admin out
# (broken firewall, missing service, mangled local config). It must
# NOT fire for a REMOTE-PENDING condition: when this CHR's local
# config is correct but the panel host (wg-mgmt) or the proxy
# (wg-data) has not yet added THIS CHR's peer, there is simply no
# handshake YET. Reverting in that case would DESTROY the correct
# local config the remote side is about to start talking to -- the
# exact wrong move. Those conditions self-heal:
#   * wg-mgmt peer: panel autosync reconcile_panel_host() (every ~2m)
#   * wg-data peer: proxy polls GET /api/proxy/wg-peers and adds it
#
# So handshake/ping liveness (old checks 2 + 4) is now tracked in a
# SEPARATE pending-remote channel that is REPORTED but never arms the
# rollback. Only LOCAL checks (endpoint present, firewall, services,
# break-glass) gate the rollback.
:global hobePendingRemote false
:global hobePendingReason ""

# (1) wg-mgmt peer endpoint-address non-empty (BUG A signal) -- LOCAL.
:if (!$hobeWgValidationOk) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ("(1) endpoint validation: " . $hobeWgValidationDetail)
}

# (2) wg-mgmt liveness: handshake OR ping to the panel -- REMOTE-PENDING.
# fix/script-service-get-guard -- length-guard the peer find BEFORE get;
# if the peer add at section 2 misfired, the unguarded get would halt
# the import with an invalid-internal-item-number error.
# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- a missing handshake here means the
# PANEL host has not added this CHR's wg-mgmt peer yet (remote pending),
# NOT a local failure. It is recorded as pending, NOT rollback-gating.
:local mgmtAlive false
:local mgmtPeerRefHs [/interface wireguard peers find comment="hobe-fleet-mgmt"]
:if ([:len $mgmtPeerRefHs] > 0) do={
    :do {
        :local lh [/interface wireguard peers get $mgmtPeerRefHs last-handshake]
        :if ([:typeof $lh] != "nothing" && [:tostr $lh] != "" && [:tostr $lh] != "never") do={
            :set mgmtAlive true
        }
    } on-error={}
}
:if (!$mgmtAlive) do={
    :do {
        :local pres [/ping address={{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }} interface=wg-mgmt count=3 as-value]
        :if ([:typeof $pres] = "array") do={
            :foreach p in=$pres do={
                :if ([:typeof $p] = "array" && [:typeof ($p->"received")] != "nothing") do={
                    :if (($p->"received") > 0) do={ :set mgmtAlive true }
                }
            }
        }
    } on-error={}
}
:if (!$mgmtAlive) do={
    :set hobePendingRemote true
    :set hobePendingReason ($hobePendingReason . " (2) wg-mgmt local config OK but NO handshake/ping to {{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }} yet -- likely panel host hasn't added this CHR's wg-mgmt peer (self-heals via panel autosync); NOT reverting")
    :log warning "hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt no handshake yet -- local config present; awaiting panel-side peer (remote pending, NOT a local failure, NOT reverting)"
} else={
    :log info "hobe-fleet: wg-mgmt handshake/ping OK"
}

{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
# (3) wg-data peer endpoint-address non-empty (re-check after section 2d).
# fix/script-service-get-guard -- length-guard the peer find BEFORE get.
:local dataPeerRefV12 [/interface wireguard peers find comment="hobe-fleet-data"]
:local dataEp ""
:if ([:len $dataPeerRefV12] > 0) do={
    :set dataEp [/interface wireguard peers get $dataPeerRefV12 endpoint-address]
}
:if ([:len [:tostr $dataEp]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (3) wg-data endpoint empty")
}

# (4) wg-data liveness: handshake OR ping to proxy -- REMOTE-PENDING.
# fix/script-service-get-guard -- same length-guard as check (2).
# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- THIS was the live (4) wg-data no-
# handshake that left the broken rollback armed forever. A missing
# wg-data handshake means the PROXY has not added this CHR's wg-data
# peer yet (allowed-ips 10.98.0.X/32). The panel publishes that peer
# at GET /api/proxy/wg-peers; the proxy polls + adds it. Until then
# there is no handshake -- a REMOTE-PENDING state, NOT a local CHR
# failure. Recorded as pending, NEVER rollback-gating (reverting would
# wipe the correct local wg-data config).
:local dataAlive false
:if ([:len $dataPeerRefV12] > 0) do={
    :do {
        :local lh [/interface wireguard peers get $dataPeerRefV12 last-handshake]
        :if ([:typeof $lh] != "nothing" && [:tostr $lh] != "" && [:tostr $lh] != "never") do={
            :set dataAlive true
        }
    } on-error={}
}
:if (!$dataAlive) do={
    :do {
        :local pres [/ping address={{ PROXY_WG_ADDR }} interface=wg-data count=3 as-value]
        :if ([:typeof $pres] = "array") do={
            :foreach p in=$pres do={
                :if ([:typeof $p] = "array" && [:typeof ($p->"received")] != "nothing") do={
                    :if (($p->"received") > 0) do={ :set dataAlive true }
                }
            }
        }
    } on-error={}
}
:if (!$dataAlive) do={
    :set hobePendingRemote true
    :set hobePendingReason ($hobePendingReason . " (4) wg-data local config OK but NO handshake/ping to {{ PROXY_WG_ADDR }} yet -- likely proxy hasn't added this CHR's wg-data peer (panel publishes it at /api/proxy/wg-peers; proxy polls + adds); NOT reverting")
    :log warning "hobe-fleet: wg-data no handshake yet -- local config present; awaiting proxy-side peer (remote pending, NOT a local failure, NOT reverting)"
} else={
    :log info "hobe-fleet: wg-data handshake/ping OK"
}
{% endif %}

{% if (API_USER|default('')) and (API_PASSWORD|default('')) %}
# (5) www-ssl enabled on port {{ API_PORT|default(8443) }} scoped to PANEL/32.
# fix/script-service-get-guard-foreach -- the live halt on chr-vpn-2
# was NOT an empty find: /ip service find name="X" can return MULTIPLE
# items when an operator is actively connected via that service (the
# DYNAMIC current-connection row coexists with the STATIC service row).
# `get` on a multi-item ref raises invalid-internal-item-number, NOT
# catchable by :do on-error in some paths. The :len > 0 guard from
# the previous revision is therefore insufficient.
#
# RouterOS-safe pattern: walk /ip service, accept ONLY the non-dynamic
# (static) item matching the desired name. Each per-item get is wrapped
# in :do on-error={} so a malformed dynamic row can never halt the
# foreach. Documented in docs/fleet/CHR_PROVISIONING_SERVICE_LOOKUP_BUG.md.
:local wwwSslOk false
:local wwwSvc ""
:foreach s in=[/ip service find] do={
    :do {
        :if ([/ip service get $s name] = "www-ssl") do={
            :if ([:tostr [/ip service get $s dynamic]] != "true") do={
                :set wwwSvc $s
            }
        }
    } on-error={}
}
:if ([:len [:tostr $wwwSvc]] > 0) do={
    :do {
        :local enabled [/ip service get $wwwSvc disabled]
        :local port [/ip service get $wwwSvc port]
        :local addr [/ip service get $wwwSvc address]
        :if ([:tostr $enabled] = "false" && [:tonum $port] = {{ API_PORT|default(8443) }} && [:find [:tostr $addr] "{{ PANEL_WG_ADDR }}"] >= 0) do={
            :set wwwSslOk true
        }
    } on-error={}
} else={
    :log warning "hobe-fleet: static www-ssl service not found; skipping check (5)"
}
:if (!$wwwSslOk) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (5) www-ssl not enabled/scoped on {{ API_PORT|default(8443) }}")
}

# (6) Firewall has the api-ssl allow from panel wg-mgmt.
:if ([:len [/ip firewall filter find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-api-ssl"]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (6) firewall hobe-fleet-fw-api-ssl missing")
}
{% endif %}

# (7) Firewall has the final drop rule.
:if ([:len [/ip firewall filter find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last"]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (7) firewall hobe-fleet-fw-drop-last missing")
}

# (8) Defence-in-depth: no-public-radius rule present (or radius role off).
{% if 'radius_transport' in ROLES %}
:if ([:len [/ip firewall filter find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-no-public-radius"]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (8) no-public-radius drop missing")
}
{% endif %}

# (9) Break-glass: hobe-open-winbox exists.
:if ([:len [/system script find name="hobe-open-winbox"]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (9) hobe-open-winbox missing")
}

# (10) Break-glass: hobe-close-winbox exists (BUG G - must exist
#      BEFORE open arms a scheduler that runs it).
:if ([:len [/system script find name="hobe-close-winbox"]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (10) hobe-close-winbox missing -- BUG G safeguard")
}

# (11) If break-glass open is active right now, the auto-close
#      scheduler MUST exist (else the surface stays open forever).
:local breakGlassActive false
:if ([:len [/ip firewall filter find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-break-glass"]] > 0) do={
    :set breakGlassActive true
}
:if ($breakGlassActive && [:len [/system scheduler find name="hobe-close-winbox-auto"]] = 0) do={
    :set hobeRollbackOk false
    :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (11) break-glass open but auto-close scheduler missing")
}

# (12) No public WinBox open unless emergency mode active. In normal
#      mode /ip service winbox address must NOT be 0.0.0.0/0.
# fix/script-service-get-guard-foreach -- this was the EXACT line that
# halted the owner's import. /ip service find name="winbox" returned
# TWO items: the static service row AND a dynamic current-connection
# row (the operator was connected via WinBox at the time, visible as
# "15 D c name=winbox ... remote=..." in /ip service print). `get` on
# a multi-item ref raises invalid-internal-item-number, NOT catchable
# by :do on-error. The foreach-skip-dynamic walk below picks only the
# static row so the import never halts mid-validation. See docs/fleet/
# CHR_PROVISIONING_SERVICE_LOOKUP_BUG.md.
:local winboxAddr ""
:local wbSvc ""
:foreach s in=[/ip service find] do={
    :do {
        :if ([/ip service get $s name] = "winbox") do={
            :if ([:tostr [/ip service get $s dynamic]] != "true") do={
                :set wbSvc $s
            }
        }
    } on-error={}
}
:if ([:len [:tostr $wbSvc]] > 0) do={
    :do { :set winboxAddr [/ip service get $wbSvc address] } on-error={}
} else={
    :log warning "hobe-fleet: static winbox service not found; skipping check (12)"
}
:if (!$breakGlassActive && [:find [:tostr $winboxAddr] "0.0.0.0/0"] >= 0) do={
    # Tolerate the emergency-admin branch (wg-mgmt unreachable +
    # OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS unset) which intentionally opens both layers.
    :if ([:len [/ip firewall filter find comment="hobe-fleet-fw-temp-emergency-admin"]] = 0) do={
        :set hobeRollbackOk false
        :set hobeRollbackReason ($hobeRollbackReason . " (12) public winbox open without emergency mode")
    }
}

# fix/chr-rollback-wgdata-rest -- the cancel decision is now based on
# LOCAL checks ONLY (hobeRollbackOk). Remote-pending handshake state
# (hobePendingRemote) is REPORTED but never blocks the cancel, so a
# clean local apply keeps its config and waits for the panel/proxy to
# add this CHR's peers instead of reverting every {{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }}.
:if ($hobeRollbackOk) do={
    :do { /system scheduler remove [find name="hobe-fleet-rollback"] } on-error={}
    :do { /file remove [find name="hobe-fleet-pre-apply.backup"] } on-error={}
    :log info "hobe-fleet: rollback guard CANCELLED -- all LOCAL validation checks passed."
    :if ($hobePendingRemote) do={
        :log warning ("hobe-fleet: apply LOCALLY complete but REMOTE peer(s) PENDING --" . $hobePendingReason)
        :put ("hobe-fleet: validation PASSED locally -- rollback cancelled. PENDING remote peer activation:" . $hobePendingReason)
        :put "hobe-fleet: this is EXPECTED right after onboarding -- the panel adds the wg-mgmt peer (autosync) and the proxy adds the wg-data peer (polls /api/proxy/wg-peers). Handshake appears within ~2 minutes. No action needed unless it persists."
    } else={
        :put "hobe-fleet: validation PASSED -- rollback cancelled. Apply complete (both tunnels handshaking)."
    }
} else={
    :log error ("hobe-fleet: LOCAL VALIDATION FAILED -- rollback LEFT ARMED. reason=" . $hobeRollbackReason)
    :put ("hobe-fleet: LOCAL VALIDATION FAILED -- rollback LEFT ARMED at T+{{ SAFEMODE_ROLLBACK_DELAY }} (ONE-SHOT). Reason:" . $hobeRollbackReason)
    :put "hobe-fleet: if you do NOT want the CHR to revert, run /system scheduler remove [find name=hobe-fleet-rollback] manually within the window. The guard fires ONCE then self-removes."
}

# ============================================================
# 13. POST-IMPORT VALIDATION DUMP
# ============================================================
# Operator sees this after `/import file=` finishes -- confirms the
# final on-CHR state without needing a separate inspection session.
:put ""
:put "==================================================================="
:put "  hobe-fleet validation -- post-import state on this CHR"
:put "==================================================================="
:put ""
:put "[/ip service print detail]"
/ip service print detail
:put ""
:put "[/ip firewall filter print]"
/ip firewall filter print
:put ""
:put "[/interface print]"
/interface print
:put ""
:put "[/ip address print]"
/ip address print
:put ""
:put "[/log print where message~\"hobe-fleet\"]"
/log print where message~"hobe-fleet"
:put ""
:put "[/system script print where name~\"hobe-\"]"
/system script print where name~"hobe-"
:put ""
:put "==================================================================="
:put "  MANUAL-ACCESS GUARANTEE -- how to reach WinBox manually"
:put "==================================================================="
{% if OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS|default('') %}
:put "  1) NORMAL: WinBox/SSH allowed from PANEL_WG_ADDR/32 + your"
:put "     configured OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS ({{ OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS }})."
{% else %}
:put "  1) NORMAL: WinBox/SSH allowed from PANEL_WG_ADDR/32 only."
:put "     (OPERATOR_ADMIN_IPS is empty -- set it on the panel under"
:put "     Settings -> Fleet Infrastructure -> Admin IPs to allow"
:put "     WinBox from your own IP, then re-export this script.)"
{% endif %}
:put "  2) BREAK-GLASS (if locked out): open the VPS provider"
:put "     console (Hetzner / NovoServe VNC or Serial) -- it bypasses"
:put "     the network firewall entirely -- and run one of:"
:put "       /system script run hobe-open-winbox    (15 min, auto-close)"
:put "       /system script run hobe-open-webfig    (15 min, auto-close)"
:put "     The matching close scripts re-restrict immediately:"
:put "       /system script run hobe-close-winbox"
:put "       /system script run hobe-close-webfig"
:put "  3) WEBFIG (public HTML5 UI on www-ssl) is NOT supported"
:put "     after hardening: /ip service www is disabled and www-ssl"
:put "     is restricted to PANEL_WG_ADDR/32. Use the wg-mgmt REST"
:put "     path (panel) or the break-glass:"
:put "       /system script run hobe-open-webfig   (15 min, auto-close)"
:put "       /system script run hobe-close-webfig  (close immediately)"
:put "  4) Production management path is wg-mgmt (private control"
:put "     plane). The panel uses it for REST polls + provisioning."
:put "==================================================================="
:put ""
:put "==================================================================="
:put "  hobe-fleet apply finished."
:put "==================================================================="

